<a name='T-Microsoft-VisualStudio-ProjectSystem-Query-IProjectSystemQueryService'></a>
## IProjectSystemQueryService `type`

##### Namespace

Microsoft.VisualStudio.ProjectSystem.Query

##### Summary

The entry point to use the project system query APIs. It is exposed as a service inside VS.
From here, a client can get the root queryable workspace to retrieve project system data.
Note: when a major change impacting the entire object space happens, (for example, client is disconnected from Nexus server),
the original [IProjectModelQueryableSpace](#T-Microsoft-VisualStudio-ProjectSystem-Query-ProjectModel-IProjectModelQueryableSpace 'Microsoft.VisualStudio.ProjectSystem.Query.ProjectModel.IProjectModelQueryableSpace') will be disposed (and firing notification before that.)
A client is expected to retrieve a new workspace when the client connects to a new server (or opens a solution locally, in which case
it will use a server side workspace object).

Microsoft.VisualStudio.ProjectSystem.Query.QueryExecution

##### Summary

Represents a chained query data provider, which uses the result of one producer to drive another producer. The final results are coming out of the second producer.
This is used to implement an attached query, which retrieves related data of entities from the parent query. However, only the result of the attached query was used, the data
from the parent query is discarded.
